Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.58,0:00:22.79,main,Sakaki,0000,0000,0000,,They seem to be raking it in, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.29,0:00:29.94,main,Sakaki,0000,0000,0000,,And apparently, {\i1}someone{\i0} is taking \Na cut of these profits
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.94,0:00:33.34,main,Sakaki,0000,0000,0000,,as "rent" for providing the Sound Club\N with a base of operations.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.10,0:00:43.81,sign_986_11_Film,Building sign,0000,0000,0000,,Film
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.10,0:00:43.81,main,K,0000,0000,0000,,Our screening at the culture \Nfestival was a success,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.12,0:00:47.37,sign_1082_15_Anime_Proposal_B,Script signs,0000,0000,0000,,Anime Proposal\NBoiled Tofu Club
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.12,0:00:47.37,sign_1082_16_Anime_Proposal_b,Script signs,0000,0000,0000,,Anime Proposal\Nby the Sepak Takraw Club
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.31,0:00:47.81,main,K,0000,0000,0000,,which has resulted in \Nrequests from several clubs
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.81,0:00:51.53,main,K,0000,0000,0000,,who want a promotional movie like \Nwhat we did for the robot club.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.49,0:00:54.61,main,K,0000,0000,0000,,The boiled tofu group, the hula dance club,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.61,0:00:57.07,main,K,0000,0000,0000,,the sepak takraw club,\N the choju-giga art restoration club...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.07,0:00:59.08,main,K,0000,0000,0000,,The carbohydrates revolution has sent
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.08,0:01:03.75,main,K,0000,0000,0000,,us a proposal titled \N"It's Electro-Magnetic Amoeba World!"
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.75,0:01:04.85,main,M,0000,0000,0000,,That sounds great!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.85,0:01:06.94,main,A,0000,0000,0000,,Let's do it! Let's accept them all—
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.09,0:01:08.27,top,K,0000,0000,0000,,But I turned them all down!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.70,0:01:10.67,main,A,0000,0000,0000,,Have you lost your mind, Kanamori?!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.94,0:01:30.40,sign_1725_26_Eizouken_Produce,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Eizouken-Produced Robot Anime\N DVD Sales & Earnings\N\N Robot Research Club (Client)\N Earnings: 51,000 yen\N\N Eizouken (15%)\N Earnings 9,000 Yen\N Contract for DVD Production, Sales,\N other associated fees\N\N Eizouken- 10,120 yen\N 9,000+10,120 (19,120 yen)
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.94,0:01:17.75,main,K,0000,0000,0000,,The DVD of the robot anime sold \N120 copies at a price of 500 yen apiece,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.75,0:01:21.94,main,K,0000,0000,0000,,of which the eizouken only \Ncame away with 15%—9,000 yen.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.94,0:01:24.60,main,K,0000,0000,0000,,This is because the rights to the film \Nbelong to the commissioning client,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.60,0:01:26.41,main,K,0000,0000,0000,,the robot club.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.41,0:01:28.29,main,K,0000,0000,0000,,Even with additional fees for our efforts,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.29,0:01:30.40,main,K,0000,0000,0000,,we walked away with just under 20,000 yen.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.19,0:01:34.65,main,K,0000,0000,0000,,But the fact of the matter is, \Nat an hourly salary of 1,000 yen,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.65,0:01:37.66,main,K,0000,0000,0000,,we put in enough labor to earn 1.8 million yen!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.01,0:01:40.53,main,A,0000,0000,0000,,1.8 m-million yen?!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.53,0:01:42.53,main,K,0000,0000,0000,,We're students, so it's ultimately fine,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.53,0:01:46.05,main,K,0000,0000,0000,,but I consider it to be a \Nmajor loss for our club.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.05,0:01:47.25,main,A,0000,0000,0000,,That's rough.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.25,0:01:49.84,main,K,0000,0000,0000,,Business done under a school's jurisdiction \Nhas certain pricing expectations
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.84,0:01:51.59,main,K,0000,0000,0000,,and budgetary constraints
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.59,0:01:53.57,main,K,0000,0000,0000,,which limit the individual unit price.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.57,0:01:56.70,main,K,0000,0000,0000,,Add the limitations of doing a \Nmovie for an extracurricular group,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.70,0:01:58.17,main,K,0000,0000,0000,,and that limits our potential even further.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.63,0:02:03.14,sign_2821_43_Anime_Proposal,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\frz-13\fax-0.82\move(405,100,505,100)}Anime Proposal
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.63,0:02:03.14,sign_2821_44_Carbohydrates_Re,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\frz-21.44\fax-0.54\move(185,230,280,230)}Carbohydrates Revolution Group
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.17,0:02:00.30,main,K,0000,0000,0000,,Unless we're working for a \Nparticularly popular group,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.30,0:02:02.33,main,K,0000,0000,0000,,that means the earnings are going to be thin.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.33,0:02:06.05,main,K,0000,0000,0000,,So for the reasons I just explained, \NI turned down all the offers we received.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.47,0:02:07.99,main,A,0000,0000,0000,,M-Makes sense...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.99,0:02:10.92,main,K,0000,0000,0000,,To make up for our loss with this incident,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.92,0:02:13.99,main,K,0000,0000,0000,,if we sold our DVDs at 1,000 yen a piece,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.99,0:02:17.06,main,K,0000,0000,0000,,we would still need to sell 1,780 copies.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.31,0:02:19.99,main,A,0000,0000,0000,,Well, that ain't happening!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.99,0:02:20.99,main,M,0000,0000,0000,,Nope.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.99,0:02:24.20,main,K,0000,0000,0000,,And yet, look at what I found.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.63,0:02:29.21,main,M,0000,0000,0000,,"Self-Publishing Exhibition \Nand Sales Event..."
