Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.23,0:04:16.96,main,M,0000,0000,0000,,That building looks like a piece of shortcake!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.96,0:04:20.75,main,A,0000,0000,0000,,This leads to the mountain shrine, \Nso I'd guess it was Main Street originally,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.75,0:04:23.95,main,A,0000,0000,0000,,but the highway was headed in \Nthat direction, and cut it off!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.28,0:04:26.91,main,M,0000,0000,0000,,This looks like a bridge, \Nbut there's no river.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.91,0:04:28.81,main,A,0000,0000,0000,,Correct! There {\i1}used{\i0} to be a river.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.81,0:04:31.14,main,A,0000,0000,0000,,That's part of why the roads meander so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.14,0:04:32.46,main,A,0000,0000,0000,,Gives it a particular feel!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.18,0:04:42.23,main,A,0000,0000,0000,,Behold! Those poles will \Nsplit open, firing a missile!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.70,0:04:50.18,main,M,0000,0000,0000,,Look at those! Like the top of tanks!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.97,0:04:53.75,main,A,0000,0000,0000,,A colossus that no one can see!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.94,0:04:57.31,main,A,0000,0000,0000,,Gigantic creatures!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.81,0:04:59.85,main,A,0000,0000,0000,,Mobilize the gantry cranes!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.07,0:05:04.82,main,M,0000,0000,0000,,I always used to imagine this \Nstuff on the way home from school.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.41,0:05:08.66,main,A,0000,0000,0000,,Scorching...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.04,0:05:16.41,main,M,0000,0000,0000,,We're gonna get sunburnt.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.41,0:05:18.10,main,A,0000,0000,0000,,The dimensional phase-shift vessel!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.63,0:05:27.09,main,A,0000,0000,0000,,The water level's risen...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.09,0:05:28.51,main,A,0000,0000,0000,,Must be from all the rain yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.13,0:05:30.86,main,A,0000,0000,0000,,It acts like a natural refrigerator...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.86,0:05:34.35,main,K,0000,0000,0000,,Stop dawdling, Asakusa. It's obnoxious.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.35,0:05:38.42,main,M,0000,0000,0000,,Gotta say, I wasn't expecting you to suggest \Nwe go out of our way for lunch, Kanamori.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.42,0:05:40.41,main,M,0000,0000,0000,,You'd normally say it's a waste of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.41,0:05:42.02,main,A,0000,0000,0000,,You're up to something, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.81,0:05:44.11,main,M,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, what's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.11,0:05:46.26,main,A,0000,0000,0000,,It's an offering. For kappas.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.26,0:05:47.28,main,M,0000,0000,0000,,Kappas?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.28,0:05:51.71,main,K,0000,0000,0000,,There are apparently legends about \Nkappas having inhabited Shibahama.
